(718,1,"2018-03-04 22:29:37","2018-03-05 02:29:37","[date]\r\n[inside]\r\n\r\nVaynerMedia Studio team,\r\n\r\nI recently checked the VaynerMedia site to see what the company is up to and I found a job listing seeking a freelance animation producer. I\'m a great candidate for this position and would love to talk to your team about the opportunity.\r\n\r\nI am a producer of animation, code and music. Here\'s my [project id=\"reel\" media=\"video\"]animation reel[/project]. I am very experienced organizing and executing both large, high-budget projects that involve a large number of teams and quick projects that are experimental with small, focused teams. I\'ve also worked extensively as a website designer/developer, so I understand the best modern strategies for incorporating animation into web. Here is my [project id=\"portfolio\" media=\"link\"]design / web portfolio[/project].\r\n\r\nBefore becoming a freelancer, I worked as a producer / project manager at an NYC-based agency called [a href=\"http://sanbornagency.com/\"]Sanborn[/a]. There, I managed technical and creative teams and worked with clients like Vogue, Drugfree.org, Condé Nast, Women\'s Health & Men\'s Health Magazines, GQ & Vanity Fair to create web projects, videos, animation, and live digital installation.\r\n\r\nI currently live in NYC working freelance on design, code and animation projects. I recently finished producing animation for a new YouTube pilot for Chicken Soup for the Soul that has yet to be released, but my most extensive animation production was my music / animation project, Dolphinhood. I made [project id=\"prelude\" media=\"video\"]episodes[/project] and [project id=\"benefits\" media=\"video\"]music videos[/project] for that cartoon.\r\n\r\nI\'ve also produced some conceptual & experimental animation projects like an Instagram Stories interview series called [project id=\"finding\" media=\"link\"]Hallway Finding[/project] and a 2D 360° music video for one of the Dolphinhood songs, [p